parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a potential problem with the airbag system, which can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the airbag warning light flashes
the airbag warning light illuminates intermittently
the airbag warning light is accompanied by other warning lights or messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbags fail to deploy in a crash
the airbags deploy unexpectedly
the airbags deploy partially
the airbags do not deploy despite the severity of the crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag system can lead to the failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag system is malfunctioning
the airbag system is faulty
the airbag system is defective
the airbag system is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift gears
the engine RPMs increase or decrease abnormally
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
and unusual noises or burning smells are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle burns excessive oil
the oil level drops rapidly
the engine makes unusual noises or produces excessive smoke
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's lights or accessories malfunction
the battery drains rapidly
the vehicle's electrical systems fail to function
and unusual noises or burning smells are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failures can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes do not function properly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
and unusual noises or vibrations are present.
